/ Main jumbotron for a primary marketing message or call to action 
.jumbotron
  .container
    .text-info
      %h1
        Decision<em>Flex</em>
    %p
      Simple to use, emergent decision making in Unity3D

.container

  = partial('signup', :locals => {:desc => "Decision<em>Flex</em> isn't out yet. Sign up to our newsletter and we'll let you know the second it's available."})

  %hr
  .row
    .col-md-12
      %h1.text-center
        What does Decision<em>Flex</em> do?
  .row
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/iperson.png", :alt => "Eat Drink Work Exercise"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Sims-like simulated humans deciding if their next action is eat, drink, work, exercise or sleep, based on thirst, hunger, wealth and fitness.
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/solider.png", :alt => "Targets"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Soldiers choosing the next target to attack, and with what weapon, based on weapon effectiveness, target range, and ammo count
    .clearfix.visible-sm-block        
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/bots.png", :alt => "Bot health pickup"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Bots deciding if now is a good time to pick up a health pack, based on distance to the pack and current health
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/anything.png", :alt => "Anything!"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Anywhere you need to make a decision between multiple <strong>actions</strong>, based on many <strong>considerations</strong>, Decision<em>Flex</em> will make it easy

  %hr
  .row
    .col-md-12
      %h1.text-center
        How does Decision<em>Flex</em> work?
  .row
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/utility.png", :alt => "Utility theory"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Under the hood Decision<em>Flex</em> uses Utility Theory to score each action, making it easy to compare apples to oranges
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/tools.png",
                          :alt => "Hierarchy and animation curve tools"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        It uses <strong>familiar Unity editor tools</strong>, including the hierarchy window and animation curves, in an intuitive manner
    .clearfix.visible-sm-block
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/codeeq.png", :alt => "Minimal code, no equations"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        Decision<em>Flex</em> is easy to connect to your game, with <strong>minimal scripting</strong>. It requires <strong>no</strong> complex math equations
    .col-sm-6.col-lg-3
      %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/emergent.png", :alt => "Emergent and alive"}
      %p.text-center.lead 
        In no time at all your game can be making <strong>emergent</strong> and <strong>human-like</strong> decisions. You can design and tweak them from the editor to get them exactly right.

  %hr

  .row
    .col-md12
      %h1.text-center
        Is there a Decision<em>Flex</em> demo?
  .row
    .col-xs-12.visible-xs.visible-sm
      %p.text-center
        (Yes, but only on wider desktop browsers)
    .content.hidden-xs.hidden-sm{:id => "unityPlayer"}
      .missing
        %a{:href => "http://unity3d.com/webplayer/", :title => "Unity Web Player. Install now!"}
          %img{:alt => "Unity Web Player. Install now!", :src => "http://webplayer.unity3d.com/installation/getunity.png", :width => "193", :height => "63"}
                
  %hr
  = partial('signup', :locals => {:desc => "Decision<em>Flex</em> isn't out yet. Sign up to our newsletter and we'll let you know the second it's available."})

  %hr
  .row
    .col-md-12
      %h1.text-center
        What does Decision<em>Flex</em> look like in action?
  .row
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/hierarchy-shot.png", :alt => "Hierarchy of multiple decisions"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Hierarchy
          %p.lead
            The hierarchy lays out the decision, its actions, and the considerations for each action. It's easy to construct and read.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/considerations-shot.png", :alt => "Animation curves weighing considerations"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Considerations
          %p.lead
            Tell Decision<em>Flex</em> how to weigh the factors influencing each action. Use animation curves to easily compare apples to oranges. No complex maths necessary.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/docs-shot.png", :alt => "Fast and smooth"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Source code, examples, and documentation
          %p.lead
            Comes with the full DF C# source, three wide-ranging example scenes, a tutorial and comprehensive documentation to get you up and running as fast as possible.
    .col-md-6
      .thumbnail
        %img.img-responsive{:src => "images/optimised-header.png", :alt => "Fast and smooth"}
        .caption
          %h3
            Optimised
          %p.lead
            Decision<em>Flex</em> runs fast with no allocations out of the box. It copes with pooling. It has tools to timeslice decisions for predictiability and budgeting. 
      
